rdf:Description.skos:definition: The collection of instances of MusicalComposition that are "song-like" in nature. They usually have lyrics and are relatively short in duration. An example of an instance of this collection is "Let it be" by TheBeatles_MusicGroup. Negative examples might be the 2nd movement of some classical symphony.

A specialization of Person. Each instance of this collection is a person who produces or performs works of art. This includes performing artists (whose works are transitory unless recorded) as well as visual artists, literary writers, and composers (whose works are intended to last for a significant length of time and be viewed or otherwise appreciated after the artist finishes them). A notable specialization of this collection is Artist_Visual. See also ArtObject, artisticWorksCreated.
